name: 노라몀/느라면
definitions:
  - slug: result-of-consistency
    name: Result of Consistency
    english_alternatives: if you keep doing X
    meaning: Expresses a result that can happen when an action is done consistently.
    examples:
      - type: simple
        sentence: 열심히 사<f>노라면</f> 좋은 날도 있겠지. 
        translated: If you work hard, good days will come.
        audio_url: 
      - type: simple
        sentence: 홈쇼핑을 보고 있<f>노라면</f> 언제 시간이 갔는지 알 수 없을 지경이었다.
        translated: When I was watching home shopping channels, I couldn't tell when time passed.
        audio_url: 
      - type: simple
        sentence: 어머니 사진을 보<f>느라면</f>, 어머니가 보고 싶어져요.
        translated: Whenever I look at my mother's photo, I miss her.
        audio_url: 
metadata:
  type: composite
details: |-
# Usage {#usage}
- It can be replaced by <f>다(가) 보면</f>.
- It sounds a bit old fashioned, so it is less commonly used than <f>다(가) 보면</f> nowadays.
- <f>느라면</f> is a less commonly used form of <f>노라면</f>.
